zhoneIsdn.name: zhoneIsdn

revisions.description: V01.00.02 - Add additional loopback types and added line-power for Malc ULC.

zhoneIsdn.description: ISDN BRI S/T Interface MIB module. This MIB manages the ISDN BRI S/T Interface on Zedge .

zhoneIsdnTrap.name: zhoneIsdnTrap
zhoneIsdnTrap.description: Trap for zedge to be sent to ZMS for far end code violation.

isdnMibV2Traps.name: isdnMibV2Traps
isdnMibV2Traps.description: This object identity adds a zero(0) for the next to last sub-identifier which should be used for new SNMPv2 Traps.

isdnTrapFrameSynchLoss.name: isdnTrapFrameSynchLoss
isdnTrapFrameSynchLoss.description: When the driver receives three successive out of synch frames then it will set the frame synch loss bit to true and then the application will send a trap to the NMS. After this when the driver detects 5 good frames then it will set the frame synch lossbit to false.

isdnTrapAmiViolations.name: isdnTrapAmiViolations
isdnTrapAmiViolations.description: Bad Ami violation Trap. If number of ami violation crosses the isdnThresholdAmiViolations then the application will send this to NMS.

isdnTrapUnbalancedFrame.name: isdnTrapUnbalancedFrame
isdnTrapUnbalancedFrame.description: This trap will be sent to NMS after the isdnThresholdUnbalancedFrame value is crossed.

isdnConfigTable.name: isdnConfigTable
isdnConfigTable.description: The ISDN BRI integrated S/T Interface Configuration Table. This table is indexed by IfIndex.It is created by aplication when the system comes up with default values.

isdnConfigEntry.name: isdnConfigEntry
isdnConfigEntry.description: An entry in the ISDN config table for each S/T Interface.

isdnLineTermClass.name: isdnLineTermClass
isdnLineTermClass.description: NT Terminal Mode.clas1 and class2 operations are as per CCITT I.430, ETSI ETS 300012, and ANSI T1.605 .These specification mandate two classes of operation for a TE with respect to D channel operation class1 : class1 is the higher class , used for signalling information class2 : This is the lower class. The default value is class1.

isdnActivationTimer2.name: isdnActivationTimer2
isdnActivationTimer2.description: Value of Activation Timer #2. t2-50ms(1): select 50ms for timer #2 t2-100ms(2): select 1000ms for timer #2 The default value is t2-50ms

isdnLineLoopBack.name: isdnLineLoopBack
isdnLineLoopBack.description: loop-back-none(1) :no loop back . loop-back-b1-st-tr(2): transparaent loopback on the S/T interface towards the user(B1 chanel). loop-back-b1-st-nt(3): non-transparent loopback onthe S/T interface towards the user(B1 chanel).. loop-back-b2-st-tr(4) :transparaent loopback on the S/T interface towards the user(B2 chanel). loop-back-b2-st-nt(5):non-transparent loopback on the S/T interface towards the user(B2 channel) loop-back-b1-idl2-tr(6):transparaent loopback on the IDL2 interface towards the system(B1 channel) loop-back-b1-idl2-nt(7):non-transparent loopback on the IDL2 interface towards the system(B1 channel) loop-back-b2-idl2-tr(8):transparaent loopback on the IDL2 interface towards the system(B2 channel) loop-back-b2-idl2-nt(9): non-transparent loopback on the IDL2 interface towards the system(B2 channel) loop-back-2bd-idl2-tr(10): transparent loopback on the IDL2 towards the system(2B + D channel) loop-back-2bd-idl2-nt(11): non-transparent loopback on the IDL2 towards the system(2B + D channel) loop-back-2bd-u-interface-tr (12): transparent loopback on the U interface towards the user(2B + D channel) loop-back-2bd-u-interface-nt (13): non-transparent loopback on the U interface(2B + D channel) loop-back-2bd-external-analog(14): loopback on the external analog interface towards the user(2B + D channel) st is loopback on the S/T interface towards the user. idl2 is loopback on the IDL2 interface towards the system. tr is transparent loopback. nt is non-transparent loopback. The default value is loop-back-none.

isdnLinePower.name: isdnLinePower
isdnLinePower.description: State of the line power. off - no power on line. sealing - minimum current on line to preclude corrosion. powering - full current on line.

isdnPerfDataCurrentTable.name: isdnPerfDataCurrentTable
isdnPerfDataCurrentTable.description: The ISDN BRI S/T interface performance table which contains the performance data for curent 15 minutes. It contains information about the status of the ISDN S/T interface, including the error statistics.

isdnPerfDataCurrentEntry.name: isdnPerfDataCurrentEntry
isdnPerfDataCurrentEntry.description: An entry in current performance table for each ISDN BRI S/T interface for last 15 minutes.

isdnPerfCurBadAmiViolation.name: isdnPerfCurBadAmiViolation
isdnPerfCurBadAmiViolation.description: Current count of frames with incorrect number of AMI violations.

isdnPerfCurTimeElapsed.name: isdnPerfCurTimeElapsed
isdnPerfCurTimeElapsed.description: In the current 15 Min period number of seconds elapsed that these counts represent.

isdnPerfDataPreviousTable.name: isdnPerfDataPreviousTable
isdnPerfDataPreviousTable.description: The ISDN BRI S/T interface performance table, it contains statistics and information about the status of the ISDN S/T interface, including the error statistics for previous 15 minutes.

isdnPerfDataPreviousEntry.name: isdnPerfDataPreviousEntry
isdnPerfDataPreviousEntry.description: An entry in Previous performance table(for last 15 minutes before the current performance period) for each S/T interface.

isdnPerfPrevBadAmiViolation.name: isdnPerfPrevBadAmiViolation
isdnPerfPrevBadAmiViolation.description: count of frames with incorrect number of AMI violations in previous 15 minutes.

isdnPerfPrevUnbalancedFrame.name: isdnPerfPrevUnbalancedFrame
isdnPerfPrevUnbalancedFrame.description: In previous 15 minutes ,count of unbalanced frames.

isdnPerPrevFsyncSeconds.name: isdnPerPrevFsyncSeconds
isdnPerPrevFsyncSeconds.description: Frame synch error seconds in previous 15 minues.

isdnPerfPrevErrorSeconds.name: isdnPerfPrevErrorSeconds
isdnPerfPrevErrorSeconds.description: In previous 15 minutes ISDN Activation error seconds

isdnPerfDataTotalTable.name: isdnPerfDataTotalTable
isdnPerfDataTotalTable.description: The ISDN BRI S/T interface performance table, it contains statistics and information about the status of the ISDN S/T interface, including the error statistics for up to the the last 24 hours. This is maintained in 15 minute intervals NOT including the current interval being accumulated. When the current period reaches 15 minutes, it's counts are rolled into the previous entry and added to these values. The 97th entry, previous to the 24 hour period is no longer included in these counts.

isdnPerfDataTotalEntry.name: isdnPerfDataTotalEntry
isdnPerfDataTotalEntry.description: An entry in total performance table for each S/T interface.

isdnPerfTotalBadAmiViolation.name: isdnPerfTotalBadAmiViolation
isdnPerfTotalBadAmiViolation.description: Total count of frames with incorrect number of AMI violations.

isdnPerfTotalTimePeriodsElapsed.name: isdnPerfTotalTimePeriodsElapsed
isdnPerfTotalTimePeriodsElapsed.description: Number of 15 minute time periods that have been used in the performance total table. This value is normally 96 indicating a valid 24 hour time period except in the cases of a restart of this agent.

isdnAlarmProfileTable.name: isdnAlarmProfileTable
isdnAlarmProfileTable.description: This table contains information for Alarm conditions. The table is indexed by IfIndex . The alarm profile will be set per port basis usig ifIndex by the application when the system comes up. The operator can not create the profile , he can only change it .

isdnThresholdAmiViolations.name: isdnThresholdAmiViolations
isdnThresholdAmiViolations.description: Threshold for number of AMI violation . If the number of violations cross this threshold then the notification is sent to NMS. 0 will disable the trap. The default value is 0. There is no range speciffied for this.

isdnThresholdUnbalancedFrame.name: isdnThresholdUnbalancedFrame
isdnThresholdUnbalancedFrame.description: Threshold for number of unbalanced frame after which the trap will be send to NMS.0 will disable the trap. The default value is 0. There is no range speciffied for this.
